# Authentication

<SecurityDefinitions />

# Webhook
LANDR signs the webhook events sent to your endpoint. This allows you to ensure that the event was sent by LANDR and not a third party. To configure your webhook or to fetch webhook details, see the <a href="#operation/Webhook_ConfigureWebhook">webhook api section</a> below.
## Verifying signatures
LANDR generates a signature by computing the hash (HMAC/SHA-256) of the http request's body using the secret key that was generated upon webhook configuration. The signature is located in the http request's header with key <code>x-signature</code>. The following pseudo code shows how the signature can be validated against the request body:

NB: The secret given by LANDR when configuring the webhook is encoded in base64.

```javascript
function processRequest(request) {
    var secret = decodeBase64("client-secret-configured-in-landr");		
    var signature = request.getHeaders()["x-signature"];
    var bodyAsString = request.getBodyAsString();
    if(hash(bodyAsString, secret) != signature)
    	throw new Exception();
}
```

## Event types

<h3>track.status</h3>
This event is triggered upon completion of a preview or master.

```json
{
    "type": "track.status",
    "data": {
        "trackId": "...",
        "status": "completed"
    }
}
```

